29:40.361 --> 29:43.323
<i>-…fetch the best nurse they can find…</i>
<i>-</i>No!

29:47.952 --> 29:52.373
She tells you, "It's okay, son,
your endorphins will kick in soon,

29:52.457 --> 29:53.875
and you won't feel anything."

29:53.958 --> 29:57.921
And you look up at her,
amazed at her steadfastness,

29:58.880 --> 30:01.758
<i>her bravery, and you realize</i>
<i>you have to have her.</i>

30:01.841 --> 30:03.384
<i>Right then and there.</i>

30:24.989 --> 30:25.907
Then what happens?

30:27.283 --> 30:28.326
So then…

30:36.709 --> 30:39.504
you make sex with her like a stallion.

30:40.171 --> 30:41.047
Excuse me?

30:42.090 --> 30:45.176
You have intercourse with her
the way a horse would.

30:45.260 --> 30:46.636
You mean I fuck you from behind?

30:47.011 --> 30:48.721
Yes, that's what I just said.

30:57.313 --> 30:58.147
That's right.

31:00.650 --> 31:04.904
Your hands are not soft and comforting.

31:05.488 --> 31:06.698
<i>They are coarse.</i>

31:07.448 --> 31:08.825
<i>You are rough.</i>

31:08.908 --> 31:12.161
You fill her up with your manhood. You…

31:21.796 --> 31:22.922
Whoo!

31:27.635 --> 31:28.469
Thank you.

31:29.429 --> 31:30.555
That was nice.

31:32.181 --> 31:33.850
-Let me pour you a drink.

31:33.933 --> 31:35.935
I'll have one in my room, thanks.

31:36.352 --> 31:38.313
Should we make this a regular thing?

31:38.730 --> 31:41.816
Well, it sure took the edge off of my day,
I'll tell you that much.

31:42.400 --> 31:43.943
Rough day at the office?

31:44.027 --> 31:46.571
Ah, just a lot of cat and mouse,

31:46.654 --> 31:49.407
chasing a dirty Pinoy all over creation.

31:53.077 --> 31:54.454
Thanks again.

31:56.164 --> 31:58.416
My name is Mildred, by the way.

31:59.417 --> 32:02.045
So, next Wednesday, then?

32:02.128 --> 32:03.963
I don't know. Uh…

32:05.548 --> 32:07.091
I gotta say, Mildred…

32:07.884 --> 32:09.552
you were the worst lay of my whole life.

32:10.011 --> 32:10.887
And this?

32:11.387 --> 32:12.931
This is too fucking weird.

32:27.612 --> 32:30.573
I looked in your lunch pail.
You didn't touch your aspic.

32:31.157 --> 32:31.991
Oh.

32:32.075 --> 32:33.993
-Sorry.

32:34.077 --> 32:36.329
I've-- I've been
a little preoccupied lately.

32:37.830 --> 32:40.041
Fatigue, I think.

32:40.708 --> 32:42.543
Well, I have just the thing.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.505
Gerald and his wife have invited us
to join them

32:45.588 --> 32:48.049
for a lovely weekend of wine tasting
up in Napa.

32:48.549 --> 32:49.384
Hm?

32:51.302 --> 32:52.929
-When?
-Saturday.

32:54.973 --> 32:58.393
I would have asked you first,
but Gerald is chief counselor.

32:58.893 --> 33:00.269
He's the reason I made partner,

33:00.353 --> 33:02.689
and I feared if I didn't accept right away
it would be rude.

33:02.772 --> 33:05.149
Gerald says it's just a wonderful year
for cabernet.

33:05.233 --> 33:06.401
I can't do this.

33:06.484 --> 33:07.819
Can't do what?

33:07.902 --> 33:10.613
I can't live like this anymore.

33:10.947 --> 33:11.823
With you.

33:12.865 --> 33:14.492
I can't stay in this marriage.

33:17.578 --> 33:18.997
I know it was my idea.

33:19.956 --> 33:21.457
And for the last three years,

33:21.541 --> 33:24.043
this arrangement
has been very helpful for both of us.

33:24.127 --> 33:26.421
Yes, it certainly has!

33:26.504 --> 33:27.755
I made partner!

33:28.089 --> 33:30.550
You work for the governor
of the state of California!

33:30.633 --> 33:31.884
Please lower your voice.

33:31.968 --> 33:34.971
Oh, I've given you a long leash, my dear.

33:35.513 --> 33:38.391
Once a month,
you get to drive on up to Frisco,

33:38.474 --> 33:42.395
and spend the weekend in your dive bars,
and I never ask questions.

33:42.478 --> 33:43.938
And I didn't ask any questions

33:44.022 --> 33:46.816
when I walked in on you being pounded
by Bob the butcher.

33:46.899 --> 33:51.029
No you didn't, and we appreciated it,
Bob and I both.

33:51.112 --> 33:52.363
I've met someone.

33:54.115 --> 33:56.117
I don't know what her situation is.

33:57.618 --> 33:59.495
But I can't stop thinking about her.

34:02.040 --> 34:03.166
Her name is Mildred.

34:04.125 --> 34:04.959
And I…

34:08.212 --> 34:09.422
She haunts me.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.968
You're a wonderful man, Trevor.

34:15.887 --> 34:17.430
But I just know…

34:18.097 --> 34:20.516
if I don't get out of this,
I'm going to die.

34:23.853 --> 34:25.396
You're being stupid,

34:26.022 --> 34:28.399
unbelievably short-sighted.

34:29.233 --> 34:31.486
If you do this, you risk everything…

34:33.279 --> 34:35.031
for you <i>and</i> me.

34:35.615 --> 34:40.328
So, I would appreciate it if you at least
took a few days and thought this through.

34:42.205 --> 34:43.956
I think you owe me that.

34:48.544 --> 34:50.379
Now I need to take a long, hot bath,

34:50.880 --> 34:51.964
if you'll excuse me.

35:23.913 --> 35:25.456
Are you all right, Dr. Hanover?

35:27.458 --> 35:28.334
Yes.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.670
I noticed your car.

35:31.629 --> 35:36.509
Oh, yeah, just some kids with slingshots
shot some rocks at me.

35:37.135 --> 35:39.220
Well, that's just awful, Doctor.

35:39.303 --> 35:40.638
Did you get a good look at them?

35:40.721 --> 35:43.057
What? Yes. I mean, no.

35:43.141 --> 35:46.435
It doesn't matter. I'll…
I'll get the windows replaced tomorrow.

35:47.103 --> 35:48.312
What is it you needed?

35:48.396 --> 35:50.273
Are you worried they're gonna come back?

35:50.731 --> 35:51.649
Who?

35:51.732 --> 35:53.442
The children with the slingshots.

35:53.526 --> 35:55.862
Because I can alert the staff
to be on the lookout

35:55.945 --> 35:58.573
for young hoodlums coming in here
looking for trouble.

35:58.656 --> 35:59.615
No, can we not--

36:00.241 --> 36:01.117
What do you want?

36:02.201 --> 36:05.079
Well, just to give you an update
on the lesbians.

36:05.163 --> 36:07.957
Miss Blix is scheduled
for hydrotherapy this evening,

36:08.040 --> 36:12.003
and Mrs. Cartwright's treatment
went swimmingly, if you'll excuse the pun.

36:12.086 --> 36:14.213
I've just had a follow-up with her,

36:14.297 --> 36:17.800
<i>and she said</i>
<i>that all her Sapphic ideations,</i>

36:17.884 --> 36:22.680
<i>her fantasies and urges</i>
<i>and so on and so forth, have stopped.</i>

36:23.848 --> 36:25.850
<i>She's even stopped</i>
<i>having libidinous thoughts</i>

36:25.933 --> 36:29.020
<i>about the housewife next door</i>
<i>who broke up her marriage.</i>

36:32.440 --> 36:34.692
So it's a modern miracle, Doctor.

36:34.775 --> 36:36.152
Congratulations.

36:36.485 --> 36:39.947
Continue with the treatments as scheduled,
thrice weekly for two months.

36:40.031 --> 36:41.115
Anything else?

36:41.282 --> 36:42.533
Well, yes.

36:42.617 --> 36:44.285
There's the matter of Mr. Dario.

36:45.494 --> 36:46.621
What about him?

36:46.704 --> 36:48.664
Well, no one knows where he is.

36:48.748 --> 36:52.335
His niece telephoned here this morning
asking to speak with him,

36:52.919 --> 36:54.754
and when I told her
that he had been released

36:54.837 --> 36:57.798
to go to his brother's funeral,
she said he wasn't at the funeral.

36:57.882 --> 37:00.343
So, don't you think that's a little odd?

37:00.927 --> 37:02.845
-I'm so sorry to interrupt.
-I beg your pardon!

37:02.929 --> 37:04.430
We are in the middle of a conversation.

37:04.513 --> 37:05.890
I do apologize,

37:05.973 --> 37:09.936
but Doctor, you and I have an early dinner
scheduled this evening, do we not?

37:11.437 --> 37:12.313
Oh, yes.

37:12.688 --> 37:13.689
I'd forgotten.

37:14.106 --> 37:15.566
Thank you, Nurse Bucket.

37:15.650 --> 37:16.651
Dinner?

37:16.734 --> 37:19.946
Yes, Nurse Bucket. It's a meal.
Many people enjoy them.

37:20.947 --> 37:21.948
Doctor,

37:22.031 --> 37:24.784
Lord knows where Mr. Dario is.
We have a responsibility--

37:24.867 --> 37:26.827
Thank you, Nurse Bucket.

37:34.085 --> 37:35.795
I don't know what you're after,

37:35.878 --> 37:39.215
but I will not stand
for this kind of blatant disrespect.

37:45.721 --> 37:46.555
Thank you.

37:48.808 --> 37:50.184
Nurse Bucket is, uh…

37:50.268 --> 37:51.894
She's in love with you.

37:54.689 --> 37:56.107
You know that, yes?

37:58.067 --> 38:01.028
Once she finally accepts
that you don't feel the same way,

38:01.112 --> 38:03.281
she will sabotage this whole operation.

38:06.450 --> 38:07.493
Hm.

38:10.663 --> 38:12.373
Would you be interested in dinner?

38:15.918 --> 38:16.919
I know a place.

38:40.443 --> 38:42.194
Can I offer sir or madam a drink?

38:42.278 --> 38:45.031
Scotch. Thank you. Neat.

38:45.990 --> 38:46.866
The same.

38:55.458 --> 38:57.209
If I asked you a question…

38:58.544 --> 39:00.671
would you be willing to be honest with me?

39:02.840 --> 39:04.342
Why is he hunting you?

39:06.761 --> 39:07.678
Who?

39:08.262 --> 39:09.805
I asked you to be honest.

39:12.141 --> 39:13.851
Why are you being followed?

39:15.895 --> 39:16.771
I…

39:19.690 --> 39:21.859
I don't entirely know what to say.

39:21.942 --> 39:23.736
Just the truth, Doctor.

39:25.905 --> 39:28.532
You obviously committed
some sort of crime.

39:30.993 --> 39:31.994
Scotch for the lady.

39:32.078 --> 39:32.912
Thank you.

39:33.412 --> 39:34.663
And for the gentleman.

39:35.122 --> 39:35.998
Thank you.

39:43.047 --> 39:44.715
I committed a crime, too.

39:46.175 --> 39:47.093
With you.

39:48.761 --> 39:50.429
When we made Dario disappear.

39:51.472 --> 39:53.349
So, of all the people in your life…

39:55.101 --> 39:57.728
wouldn't I be the one
you could trust the most?

40:03.484 --> 40:04.735
I did a very bad thing.

40:04.819 --> 40:06.195
We all do bad things.

40:06.278 --> 40:07.113
No, but…

40:08.030 --> 40:08.864
very bad.

40:10.825 --> 40:11.700
It haunts me.

40:17.915 --> 40:18.749
Tell me.

40:28.008 --> 40:29.093
It was just, uh…

40:30.052 --> 40:31.512
a few years ago now.

40:33.597 --> 40:34.432
I thought…

40:35.099 --> 40:37.184
I thought I was invincible.

40:40.020 --> 40:41.564
I don't feel that way anymore.

40:44.358 --> 40:48.028
<i>A rich woman,</i>
<i>an heiress to a vast fortune,</i>

40:48.112 --> 40:52.533
<i>she asked me to treat her son,</i>
<i>who she believed was deranged.</i>

40:52.616 --> 40:54.994
<i>When I laid eyes on the boy,</i>
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>

40:55.077 --> 40:56.620
<i>He had the face of an angel.</i>

40:57.538 --> 40:58.956
-Lovely to meet you.
-Pleasure.

40:59.290 --> 41:01.375
<i>Polite, engaged.</i>

41:02.710 --> 41:05.337
The boy liked to prick people
with needles.

41:05.421 --> 41:08.466
It's a sexual disorder called piquerism.

41:08.966 --> 41:11.469
Mimics the penetrative aspects
of intercourse.

41:12.386 --> 41:14.180
<i>-He pricked his mother.</i>

41:15.723 --> 41:17.475
-Ow!
<i>-Pricked the cook.</i>

41:17.558 --> 41:19.768
But he was becoming more violent.

41:20.519 --> 41:24.523
He sharpened a leather punch
and stabbed the gardener.

41:25.524 --> 41:27.943
<i>He wasn't seriously injured</i>
<i>and stayed on at the job.</i>

41:32.281 --> 41:34.283
So, I took Henry on as a patient…

41:35.367 --> 41:38.954
convinced that I could find the locus
of the inciting trauma.

41:44.960 --> 41:46.337
Have you heard of lysergic acid?

41:47.922 --> 41:48.756
Hallucinogen.

41:49.340 --> 41:51.217
Physicians in Switzerland had just had

41:51.300 --> 41:54.803
some very promising
therapeutic results with LSD.

41:55.554 --> 41:58.641
It seemed to free the mind
of its workaday constraints.

42:01.143 --> 42:04.688
I told the heiress all I would need
was a full day with Henry alone,

42:05.564 --> 42:08.234
so she took a trip
to the other side of the island.

42:09.693 --> 42:12.279
And I introduced the lysergic acid
to Henry.

42:12.905 --> 42:15.241
<i>Standard dose, 20 micrograms.</i>

42:15.741 --> 42:16.742
<i>But the boy said…</i>

42:16.825 --> 42:17.785
You take some, too.

42:20.621 --> 42:23.958
<i>There was no way I was going to agree</i>
<i>with that, so I pretended.</i>

42:41.642 --> 42:42.476
There.

42:43.435 --> 42:45.604
Twenty micrograms for both of us.

42:57.491 --> 42:58.409
Okay.

43:10.879 --> 43:12.715
Okay, Henry, I'm gonna…

43:14.091 --> 43:15.759
ask you some questions, okay?

43:15.843 --> 43:18.470
And I would like you to answer
as best you can.

43:28.397 --> 43:30.065
<i>I knew right away something was wrong.</i>

43:32.776 --> 43:34.653
<i>He poured the whole thing into my drink.</i>

43:39.658 --> 43:41.702
<i>Four thousand micrograms.</i>

43:41.785 --> 43:44.163
<i>About 200 times the therapeutic dose.</i>

43:49.168 --> 43:54.048
<i>What happened from there I--</i>
<i>I can only describe as a sort of a dream.</i>

43:55.549 --> 43:57.968
<i>I was there in that room, but…</i>

44:00.262 --> 44:02.097
<i>I kept leaving my own body,</i>

44:02.765 --> 44:07.645
<i>and found myself staring at a--</i>
<i>the godhead at the center of the universe.</i>

44:08.145 --> 44:09.813
<i>And then things got very dark.</i>

44:12.608 --> 44:15.235
<i>Then he just started talking.</i>

44:15.319 --> 44:18.864
<i>It wouldn't stop,</i>
<i>it seemed to go on for months.</i>

44:20.032 --> 44:23.786
<i>He kept going on about how a deity</i>
<i>had come into his bedroom</i>

44:23.869 --> 44:29.041
<i>and stolen his arms and sewed</i>
<i>someone else's arms onto his body.</i>

44:29.124 --> 44:31.043
<i>That this is why he was so troubled.</i>

44:31.126 --> 44:34.672
<i>That… that the arms were</i>
<i>the source of his psychosis,</i>

44:35.381 --> 44:37.091
<i>and that he wished me to remove them.</i>

44:37.174 --> 44:39.009
I'm gonna be right back, okay?

44:39.093 --> 44:41.303
Don't… don't go anywhere.

44:46.266 --> 44:49.978
<i>And then he was gone</i>
<i>for what seemed like ages.</i>

44:51.146 --> 44:53.691
<i>Or like he'd never been there</i>
<i>in the first place.</i>

44:57.319 --> 44:58.696
<i>And then he returned…</i>

45:00.614 --> 45:01.699
<i>covered in blood.</i>

45:05.577 --> 45:06.495
Now…

45:07.413 --> 45:11.709
we are going to put these on me.

45:12.084 --> 45:14.586
I knew right away
they were the gardener's,

45:15.003 --> 45:16.880
and that Henry had just murdered him.

45:17.214 --> 45:18.340
Oh, my.

45:22.594 --> 45:24.304
Then I heard him screaming.

45:28.016 --> 45:30.894
<i>I watched the boy saw off his own arm.</i>

45:35.649 --> 45:40.446
<i>And when he finished, he wedged</i>
<i>his other arm behind a heavy bureau</i>

45:40.529 --> 45:42.239
<i>and cracked it at the humerus.</i>

45:46.535 --> 45:48.328
At that point I panicked.

45:49.037 --> 45:51.123
He was bleeding out,
he was going to die.

45:51.206 --> 45:52.207
Tell me you didn't.

45:52.291 --> 45:54.835
So I tried it.<i> </i>I tried it,

45:55.419 --> 45:58.213
<i>with the medical equipment</i>
<i>I had with me, and the saw.</i>

45:58.297 --> 46:00.174
<i>I sliced off the arm that was broken</i>

46:00.716 --> 46:02.843
and sewed the gardener's arms onto his.

46:04.970 --> 46:08.098
Even as it was happening,
I couldn't tell if it was real.

46:09.183 --> 46:11.268
But I didn't want him to die. I…

46:15.773 --> 46:17.775
I didn't want him to die.

46:18.817 --> 46:21.069
And I knew it couldn't work.

46:21.945 --> 46:23.614
I didn't have the tools.

46:23.697 --> 46:25.449
I couldn't fuse the bones together.

46:25.866 --> 46:27.284
The nerves were all severed.

46:27.367 --> 46:29.411
So I just tried to attach
the blood vessels,

46:29.495 --> 46:30.871
so he wouldn't bleed to death.

46:31.997 --> 46:33.665
<i>And there was Henry the whole time,</i>

46:33.749 --> 46:37.586
<i>-just laughing and thanking me.</i>
<i>-</i>

46:43.675 --> 46:48.096
When I finished, I gave him
what morphine I had, and he slept.

46:50.015 --> 46:50.849
And then I ran.

46:51.600 --> 46:54.812
I knew that his body
would reject the new limbs, of course.

46:54.895 --> 46:58.232
They would have gone gangrenous
and practically fallen right off.

46:59.817 --> 47:04.822
From what information I could gather,
Henry's system quickly went septic.

47:05.739 --> 47:07.366
He very nearly died.

47:08.992 --> 47:10.577
But in fact, he recovered.

47:14.748 --> 47:17.876
But only after the infection spread
to his legs,

47:17.960 --> 47:19.753
<i>and they, too, had to be removed.</i>

47:23.173 --> 47:24.633
His mother wants me dead.

47:27.094 --> 47:30.138
And I don't imagine it's a gentle death
she has planned.

47:35.185 --> 47:37.688
She's never going to rest
until she finds me.

47:42.442 --> 47:44.820
Then we have to make sure
that she never does.

47:46.697 --> 47:49.408
And I think I know
how that can be accomplished.
